==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wenan|wēnan]]'', from Germanic ''*waenjan''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[wanen]]'', German ''[[wähnen]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/wiːn/}}
*{{SAMPA|/wi:n/}}
* Homophone: [[wean]]
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːn|-iːn]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{archaic}} To suppose; to [[think]], [[believe]].
#*"Yet humble second shall be first, I ween" &mdash; [[Wikipedia:W. S. Gilbert|W.S. Gilbert]], ''[[Wikipedia:Princess Ida|Princess Ida]]'', 1884
# {{archaic}}  To [[expect]], [[hope]] or [[wish]].

